							<h3>Biography</h3>
			 			<!-- Insert Short Biography here. Insert between <p> and </p>. Example: <p>INSERT PARAGRAPH HERE</p>-->
								<p>I grew up on a small farm near Raymond, Alberta, Canada. I spent the first 18 years of my life on the farm and then moved down to Provo in 2002 to attend Brigham Young University, where I received my BS in Chemical Engineering. I also spent 2 years from 2003 to 2005 serving an LDS mission in France where I loved the sites and people. I am now working on receiving my PhD in Chemical Engineering. My research interests are energy and combustion related, with my dissertation focusing on ash deposition in syngas turbines.</p>
